{"word":"ἐπιτέλλω","slug":"ἐπιτέλλω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπιτέλλω</b></el> <el>(aor1 <el>ἐπ-έτειλα</el>) (<a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <el>-τέταλκα</el>) (<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <el>-τέταλμαι</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to lay upon, enjoin, prescribe, ordain, command</i>, <el>τι</el> or <el>τί τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> only, <i>to give orders to</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to order</i> him <i>to</i> do. <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>:—also in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, just like the <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>Act.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to rise</i>, of stars, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>:—<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, of love, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}